# рҹҗұ Feature Update Walkthrough

## Summary of All Changes

| # | Feature | Files Changed |
|---|---------|--------------|
| 1 | Petting bond cooldown | `CatInteraction.cs` |
| 2 | Camera zoom (not scale) when petting | `CatInteraction.cs`, **NEW** `CameraController.cs` |
| 3 | Horizontal swipe to pan | **NEW** `CameraController.cs` |
| 4 | Bowl approach only if food/water available | `CatAI.cs` |
| 5 | Need thought bubble | **NEW** `NeedBubble.cs` |
| 6 | Ground tap to call cat | `CameraController.cs`, `CatAI.cs` |
| 7 | Feather toy mode toggle | **NEW** `ToolModeManager.cs`, `DraggableToy.cs`, `CatInteraction.cs` |
| 8 | Self-grooming animation | `CatController.cs`, `CatAnimator.cs`, `CatAI.cs`, `CatNeeds.cs` |

---

## Unity Editor Setup

### 1. CameraController (Pan + Zoom + Ground Tap)

1. Select your **Main Camera** in the Hierarchy
2. **Add Component** вҶ’ `CameraController`
3. Configure in Inspector:

| Field | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Cam | (auto-detected) | |
| Cat AI | Drag your Cat GameObject | Required for ground-tap calling |
| Pan Min X / Pan Max X | `-5` / `5` | Adjust to your room width |
| Drag Threshold | `15` | Pixels before a touch counts as drag vs tap |
| Pan Sensitivity | `1` | |
| Pet Zoom Size | `3` | Smaller = more zoomed in when petting |
| Zoom Speed | `3` | How fast the zoom transitions |
| Zoom Y Offset | `0.5` | Centers slightly above the cat |

**How it works:**
- **Hand mode + drag on empty space** вҶ’ Camera pans horizontally
- **Hand mode + tap on empty space** вҶ’ Cat walks to that spot
- **Petting the cat** вҶ’ Camera smoothly zooms in, zooms back out when done

---

### 2. ToolModeManager (Hand / Feather Toggle Button)

1. Create a **Canvas** if you don't have one:
   - Hierarchy вҶ’ Right-click вҶ’ **UI вҶ’ Canvas**
   - Set Canvas Scaler to **Scale With Screen Size**, Reference Resolution `1080Г—1920`

2. Create the toggle button:
   - Right-click Canvas вҶ’ **UI вҶ’ Button**
   - Rename to `ToolModeButton`
   - Position it in the **bottom-right corner** (anchor bottom-right)
   - Size: `80Г—80` or similar
   - Remove the child `Text` object (we use icons instead)

3. Create an **empty GameObject** in the scene (or on the Canvas):
   - Rename to `ToolModeManager`
   - **Add Component** вҶ’ `ToolModeManager`
   - Configure:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Toggle Button | Drag the `ToolModeButton` |
| Button Icon | Drag the `Image` component on the button |
| Hand Icon | Assign a hand sprite (create placeholder) |
| Feather Icon | Assign a feather sprite (create placeholder) |

**How it works:**
- Tap the button вҶ’ toggles between Hand рҹ–җпёҸ and Feather рҹӘ¶
- **Hand mode**: Tap cat = pet, tap ground = call cat, drag = pan camera
- **Feather mode**: Touch/drag empty space = feather toy appears and cat chases it

---

### 3. NeedBubble (Thought Bubble Above Cat)

1. Under your **Cat GameObject**, create a child:
   - Right-click Cat вҶ’ **Create Empty** вҶ’ Rename to `NeedBubble`
   - Position: `(0.8, 1.5, 0)` (above and to the right of the cat)

2. Add a **SpriteRenderer** to `NeedBubble`:
   - Assign your thought bubble background sprite
   - Sorting Layer: same as cat, Order: above cat

3. Create a child under `NeedBubble`:
   - Right-click NeedBubble вҶ’ **Create Empty** вҶ’ Rename to `Icon`
   - Add a **SpriteRenderer** to `Icon`
   - This displays the need icon inside the bubble

4. Add the `NeedBubble` script to the `NeedBubble` object:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Cat Needs | (auto-detected from parent) |
| Bubble Renderer | The bubble background SpriteRenderer |
| Icon Renderer | The Icon child's SpriteRenderer |
| Hunger Icon | рҹҗҹ Fish or food bowl sprite |
| Thirst Icon | рҹ’§ Water drop sprite |
| Happiness Icon | рҹҳў Sad face sprite |
| Cleanliness Icon | вңЁ Sparkle or soap sprite |
| Low Threshold | `30` (shows when need drops below this) |

**Priority order**: Hunger > Thirst > Happiness > Cleanliness

The bubble fades in/out smoothly and bobs gently when visible.

---

### 4. CatAI вҖ” Updated Bowl References

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The bowl references in CatAI changed from **Transform** to **FoodBowl/WaterBowl scripts**. You need to re-assign them!

1. Select your **Cat GameObject**
2. In the `CatAI` component, find "Need-Driven Behavior":

| Old Field | New Field | What to Drag |
|---|---|---|
| ~~Food Bowl Transform~~ | **Food Bowl** | Drag the FoodBowl **GameObject** (it will pick up the script) |
| ~~Water Bowl Transform~~ | **Water Bowl** | Drag the WaterBowl **GameObject** |

Now the cat **only walks to bowls when they contain food/water**, not when empty.

---

### 5. DraggableToy вҖ” Feather Toy Setup

The DraggableToy is already in your scene. Changes to note:

- **Only active in FeatherToy mode** (automatically hides in Hand mode)
- **Any touch on empty space** in FeatherToy mode moves the feather (no need to tap the toy's collider first)
- While playing: **happiness вҶ‘**, **hunger вҶ“**, **cleanliness вҶ“**

Configure in Inspector:

| Field | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Happiness Per Second | `5` | |
| Hunger Drain Per Second | `1` | How fast hunger drops while playing |
| Cleanliness Drain Per Second | `0.5` | How fast cleanliness drops while playing |

---

### 6. Grooming Animation Setup

The grooming system is fully scripted. What you need to create:

**Sprite Art: Cat Grooming** (4-8 frames, ~3 seconds)

| Frame | Description |
|---|---|
| 1 | Cat sitting, lifting paw |
| 2 | Paw near face, starting to lick |
| 3 | Licking paw |
| 4 | Licking body/side |
| 5 | Continue grooming |
| 6 | Finishing, paw down |

**In Unity:**
1. Create animation clip `Cat_Grooming.anim` вҖ” **Loop Time: вқҢ Off**
2. In your Animator Controller:
   - Add state `Grooming` вҶ’ assign `Cat_Grooming` clip
   - Add **Any State вҶ’ Grooming** transition:
     - Condition: `State` Equals `9`
     - Has Exit Time: вқҢ Off
     - Can Transition To Self: вқҢ Off
     - Transition Duration: `0`

3. In the `CatAnimator` component on your cat, set:
   - **Grooming Duration** = match your clip length (e.g., `3.0`)

**How it works at runtime:**
```
AI decides: "time to groom" (random chance during idle, higher when dirty)
  вҶ’ CatController enters Grooming state
  вҶ’ CatAnimator plays Cat_Grooming clip + starts 3s timer
  вҶ’ Timer fires вҶ’ CatController gives +15 cleanliness вҶ’ returns to Idle
```

